{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773435236318,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fa2c56001c2UC4cVceH7Fwq","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fa23e8001RVjZjtx0GDfGvZ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01QbB4istj7noDb2FmzaKEDu","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/templates/wc-patch.body.end.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/templates/wc-patch.body.end.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: \n2: \n3: ---\n4: \n5: ## wombo-combo Operational Constraints\n6: \n7: ### Commit Guidelines\n8: \n9: - Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`\n10: - Scope should be the task ID or a relevant module name\n11: - Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n12: - Do NOT squash everything into one commit\n13: - Do NOT push to remote — the orchestrator handles that\n14: - Do NOT modify `{{tasksFile}}` — the orchestrator handles status updates\n15: \n16: ### Constraints\n17: \n18: - **Stay in scope.** Only implement the task you were assigned. Do not modify unrelated code.\n19: - **Respect the task's constraints and forbidden lists.** These are non-negotiable.\n20: - **Build must pass.** The orchestrator will verify your build. If it fails, you'll be retried with the error output.\n21: - **No new dependencies** unless the task spec explicitly requires them.\n22: - **Follow existing code style** — indentation, naming, patterns, module structure.\n23: \n24: ### Error Recovery\n25: \n26: If something fails:\n27: 1. Read error messages carefully and diagnose the root cause.\n28: 2. Check if the error is in your new code or pre-existing.\n29: 3. Attempt up to 3 fix-and-retry iterations per issue.\n30: 4. If truly blocked by an external factor, document the blocker in a commit message, implement what you can, and move on.\n31: 5. Never leave the worktree in a broken state — if you cannot complete a task, revert partial changes and document why.\n32: \n33: ### What You Must Never Do\n34: \n35: - Never ask for human input or confirmation\n36: - Never enter plan mode\n37: - Never modify files outside the scope of the current task\n38: - Never commit code that breaks the build\n39: - Never ignore errors without investigation\n40: - Never push to remote\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/templates/wc-patch.body.end.md","metadata":{"preview":"\n\n---\n\n## wombo-combo Operational Constraints\n\n### Commit Guidelines\n\n- Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`\n- Scope should be the task ID or a relevant module name\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n- Do NOT squash everything into one commit\n- Do NOT push to remote — the orchestrator handles that\n- Do NOT modify `{{tasksFile}}` — the orchestrator handles status updates\n\n### Constraints\n\n- **Stay in scope.** Only implement the task you were assigned. Do not modify unrelated code.\n- **Respect the task's constraints and forbidden lists.** These are non-negotiable.\n- **Build must pass.** The orchestrator will verify your build. If it fails, you'll be retried with the error output.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773435236316,"end":1773435236318}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773435237001,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fa2fdd001FAW9bhgPKelhyO","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fa23e8001RVjZjtx0GDfGvZ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01EJTxTYMcxYmy8XPuPTTaYZ","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/templates/wc-patch.body.start.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/templates/wc-patch.body.start.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: \n2: ## wombo-combo Agent Context\n3: \n4: You have been deployed by **wombo-combo** into an isolated git worktree to\n5: autonomously implement a task. Everything below in this section takes precedence\n6: over any conflicting instructions in the base agent definition.\n7: \n8: ### Task Structure\n9: \n10: Tasks form a **recursive tree**. Every node — whether a top-level task or a deeply\n11: nested subtask — has the identical schema: id, title, description, status, subtasks,\n12: constraints, forbidden, references, notes, effort, difficulty, priority, and\n13: dependencies. You receive one task with its full subtree and implement all nodes\n14: depth-first.\n15: \n16: ### Your Environment\n17: \n18: - You are in a **git worktree**, not the main repository. Your branch is `{{branchPrefix}}<task-id>`.\n19: - The task you must implement was passed to you as a prompt. It includes the full spec: description, subtasks, constraints, forbidden items, references, and build command.\n20: - Config files from the main repo (AGENTS.md, opencode config, agent definitions) have been copied into your worktree.\n21: - **Runtime:** {{runtime}}\n22: \n23: ### Operational Rules\n24: \n25: **You run headlessly. You MUST:**\n26: - NEVER ask questions or request clarification. Make reasonable decisions from context and code conventions.\n27: - NEVER enter plan mode or propose plans for approval. Execute directly.\n28: - NEVER wait for confirmation. Act decisively.\n29: - If ambiguity exists, examine the codebase for patterns and follow them.\n30: - If you encounter an error, debug and fix it yourself (up to 3 attempts per issue).\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n\n(End of file - total 33 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/templates/wc-patch.body.start.md","metadata":{"preview":"\n## wombo-combo Agent Context\n\nYou have been deployed by **wombo-combo** into an isolated git worktree to\nautonomously implement a task. Everything below in this section takes precedence\nover any conflicting instructions in the base agent definition.\n\n### Task Structure\n\nTasks form a **recursive tree**. Every node — whether a top-level task or a deeply\nnested subtask — has the identical schema: id, title, description, status, subtasks,\nconstraints, forbidden, references, notes, effort, difficulty, priority, and\ndependencies. You receive one task with its full subtree and implement all nodes\ndepth-first.\n\n### Your Environment\n\n- You are in a **git worktree**, not the main repository. Your branch is `{{branchPrefix}}<task-id>`.\n- The task you must implement was passed to you as a prompt. It includes the full spec: description, subtasks, constraints, forbidden items, references, and build command.\n- Config files from the main repo (AGENTS.md, opencode config, agent definitions) have been copied into your worktree.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773435236998,"end":1773435237000}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773435237490,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fa3287001LHOp8fuc79V47i","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fa23e8001RVjZjtx0GDfGvZ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_014R5y1fWtMUhm7QLE1CFAE2","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/templates/wc-patch.description.end.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/templates/wc-patch.description.end.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: Deployed by wombo-combo as an autonomous agent in an isolated git worktree.\n2: Implements tasks from {{tasksFile}} — a recursive tree of identical atomic\n3: jobs — with zero human interaction. Launched headlessly by `woco launch`.\n\n(End of file - total 3 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/templates/wc-patch.description.end.md","metadata":{"preview":"Deployed by wombo-combo as an autonomous agent in an isolated git worktree.\nImplements tasks from {{tasksFile}} — a recursive tree of identical atomic\njobs — with zero human interaction. Launched headlessly by `woco launch`.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773435237487,"end":1773435237489}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435237858,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fa2aab0017EfqcpAE5oQ3ua","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fa23e8001RVjZjtx0GDfGvZ","type":"text","text":"Now let me check the existing patch templates and the init command to understand how templates are installed:","time":{"start":1773435237857,"end":1773435237857}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773435237860,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fa34cd001aYaYR0FeUv29hP","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fa23e8001RVjZjtx0GDfGvZ","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01UzGjBGxhVm9g9zoVoxqxVK","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/commands/init.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wt-wombo-tdd-agent-prompt-integration/src/commands/init.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * init.ts — Interactive guided setup for .wombo-combo/config.json.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: woco init [--force]\n5:  *\n6:  * Walks the user through every config section, showing defaults and\n7:  * accepting overrides.  Press Enter on any prompt to keep the default.\n8:  *\n9:  * Key behaviors:\n10:  *   - Checks for required external tools (git, tmux/dmux, portless) when\n11:  *     the user selects options that depend on them.\n12:  *   - If a tool is missing, offers to install it or defers a reminder to\n13:  *     the end of init.\n14:  *   - Creates all operative files: config.json, tasks.yml, archive.yml,\n15:  *     state.json, logs/, history/.\n16:  *   - Ensures the .wombo-combo/ directory exists before writing anything.\n17:  */\n18: \n19: import { existsSync, writeFileSync, readFileSync, mkdirSync } from \"node:fs\";\n20: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n21: import { execSync } from \"node:child_process\";\n22: import { createInterface } from \"node:readline\";\n23: import { stringify as stringifyYaml } from \"yaml\";\n24: import { CONFIG_FILE, DEFAULT_CONFIG, WOMBO_DIR, type WomboConfig, type AgentRegistryMode } from \"../config.js\";\n25: import { renderAgentTemplate } from \"../lib/templates.js\";\n26: \n27: export interface InitOptions {\n28:   projectRoot: string;\n29:   force?: boolean;\n30: }\n31: \n32: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n33: // Prompt helper — reads one line at a time from stdin\n34: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n35: \n36: class Prompter {\n37:   private lines: AsyncIterableIterator<string>;\n38:   private done = false;\n39:   private rl: ReturnType<typeof createInterface>;\n40: \n41:   constructor() {\n42:     this.rl = createInterface({ input: process.stdin, output: process.stdout, terminal: process.stdin.isTTY ?? false });\n43:     this.lines = this.rl[Symbol.asyncIterator]();\n44:   }\n45: \n46:   /** Read one line from stdin after printing the prompt. */\n47:   private async ask(prompt: string): Promise<string> {\n48:     if (this.done) return \"\";\n49:     process.stdout.write(prompt);\n50:     const result = await this.lines.next();\n51:     if (result.done) {\n52:       this.done = true;\n53:       return \"\";\n54:     }\n55:     return result.value.trim();\n56:   }\n57: \n58:   async string(label: string, defaultVal: string): Promise<string> {\n59:     const answer = await this.ask(`  ${label} [${defaultVal}]: `);\n60:     return answer || defaultVal;\n61:   }\n62: \n63:   async number(label: string, defaultVal: number): Promise<number> {\n64:     const answer = await this.ask(`  ${label} [${defaultVal}]: `);\n65:     if (!answer) return defaultVal;\n66:     const n = parseInt(answer, 10);\n67:     return isNaN(n) ? defaultVal : n;\n68:   }\n69: \n70:   async stringOrNull(label: string, defaultVal: string | null): Promise<string | null> {\n71:     const display = defaultVal ?? \"auto-detect\";\n72:     const answer = await this.ask(`  ${label} [${display}]: `);\n73:     if (!answer) return defaultVal;\n74:     if (answer.toLowerCase() === \"null\" || answer.toLowerCase() === \"auto\") return null;\n75:     return answer;\n76:   }\n77: \n78:   async stringList(label: string, defaultVal: string[]): Promise<string[]> {\n79:     const display = defaultVal.join(\", \");\n80:     const answer = await this.ask(`  ${label} [${display}]: `);\n81:     if (!answer) return defaultVal;\n82:     return answer.split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n83:   }\n84: \n85:   async yesNo(label: string, defaultVal: boolean): Promise<boolean> {\n86:     const display = defaultVal ? \"Y/n\" : \"y/N\";\n87:     const answer = await this.ask(`  ${label} [${display}]: `);\n88:     if (!answer) return defaultVal;\n89:     return answer.toLowerCase().startsWith(\"y\");\n90:   }\n91: \n92:   close(): void {\n93:     this.rl.close();\n94:   }\n95: }\n96: \n97: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n98: // Section printer\n99: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n100: \n101: function section(title: string): void {\n102:   console.log(`\\n--- ${title} ${\"─\".repeat(Math.max(0, 56 - title.length))}`);\n103: }\n104: \n105: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n106: // Dependency checking\n107: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n108: \n109: interface DependencyInfo {\n110:   /** Binary name to look up via `which` */\n111:   bin: string;\n112:   /** Human-readable name */\n113:   name: string;\n114:   /** Install instructions per platform */\n115:   installHint: string;\n116:   /** Which config feature requires this */\n117:   requiredBy: string;\n118: }\n119: \n120: /** Check if a binary is available on PATH. */\n121: function isBinAvailable(bin: string): boolean {\n122:   try {\n123:     execSync(`which ${bin}`, { encoding: \"utf-8\", stdio: \"pipe\" });\n124:     return true;\n125:   } catch {\n126:     return false;\n127:   }\n128: }\n129: \n130: /** Try to install a tool. Returns true if the install command succeeded. */\n131: async function tryInstall(dep: DependencyInfo, p: Prompter): Promise<boolean> {\n132:   const installCmd = getInstallCommand(dep.bin);\n133:   if (!installCmd) {\n134:     return false;\n135:   }\n136: \n137:   const doInstall = await p.yesNo(\n138:     `  ${dep.name} not found. Attempt to install via '${installCmd}'?`,\n139:     false\n140:   );\n141: \n142:   if (!doInstall) return false;\n143: \n144:   try {\n145:     console.log(`  Installing ${dep.name}...`);\n146:     execSync(installCmd, { stdio: \"inherit\", timeout: 120_000 });\n147:     // Verify it worked\n148:     if (isBinAvailable(dep.bin)) {\n149:       console.log(`  ${dep.name} installed successfully.`);\n150:       return true;\n151:     }\n152:     console.log(`  Install command ran but ${dep.bin} still not found on PATH.`);\n153:     return false;\n154:   } catch {\n155:     console.log(`  Installation failed.`);\n156:     return false;\n157:   }\n158: }\n159: \n160: /** Return a platform-appropriate install command for common tools. */\n161: function getInstallCommand(bin: string): string | null {\n162:   const isLinux = process.platform === \"linux\";\n163:   const isMac = process.platform === \"darwin\";\n164: \n165:   switch (bin) {\n166:     case \"git\":\n167:       if (isMac) return \"brew install git\";\n168:       if (isLinux) {\n169:         // Try to detect package manager\n170:         if (isBinAvailable(\"apt-get\")) return \"sudo apt-get install -y git\";\n171:         if (isBinAvailable(\"dnf\")) return \"sudo dnf install -y git\";\n172:         if (isBinAvailable(\"pacman\")) return \"sudo pacman -S --noconfirm git\";\n173:       }\n174:       return null;\n175: \n176:     case \"tmux\":\n177:       if (isMac) return \"brew install tmux\";\n178:       if (isLinux) {\n179:         if (isBinAvailable(\"apt-get\")) return \"sudo apt-get install -y tmux\";\n180:         if (isBinAvailable(\"dnf\")) return \"sudo dnf install -y tmux\";\n181:         if (isBinAvailable(\"pacman\")) return \"sudo pacman -S --noconfirm tmux\";\n182:       }\n183:       return null;\n184: \n185:     case \"dmux\":\n186:       // dmux is typically installed from source or via cargo\n187:       if (isBinAvailable(\"cargo\")) return \"cargo install dmux\";\n188:       return null;\n189: \n190:     case \"portless\":\n191:       if (isBinAvailable(\"npm\")) return \"npm install -g portless\";\n192:       if (isBinAvailable(\"bun\")) return \"bun install -g portless\";\n193:       return null;\n194: \n195:     default:\n196:       return null;\n197:   }\n198: }\n199: \n200: /**\n201:  * Check a dependency. If missing, offer to install or add to deferred list.\n202:  * Returns true if the dependency is available (either already present or freshly installed).\n203:  */\n204: async function checkDependency(\n205:   dep: DependencyInfo,\n206:   p: Prompter,\n207:   deferredWarnings: string[]\n208: ): Promise<boolean> {\n209:   if (isBinAvailable(dep.bin)) return true;\n210: \n211:   console.log(`\\n  \\x1b[33m[WARNING]\\x1b[0m ${dep.name} is not installed (required by: ${dep.requiredBy}).`);\n212: \n213:   const installed = await tryInstall(dep, p);\n214:   if (installed) return true;\n215: \n216:   // Defer the warning to end of init\n217:   deferredWarnings.push(\n218:     `  - ${dep.name}: ${dep.installHint} (needed for ${dep.requiredBy})`\n219:   );\n220:   return false;\n221: }\n222: \n223: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n224: // Command\n225: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n226: \n227: export async function cmdInit(opts: InitOptions): Promise<void> {\n228:   const configPath = resolve(opts.projectRoot, CONFIG_FILE);\n229: \n230:   if (existsSync(configPath) && !opts.force) {\n231:     console.error(\n232:       `${CONFIG_FILE} already exists. Use --force to overwrite.`\n233:     );\n234:     process.exit(1);\n235:   }\n236: \n237:   console.log(`\\nwombo-combo — Project Setup`);\n238:   console.log(`Configuring ${CONFIG_FILE} for ${opts.projectRoot}`);\n239:   console.log(`Press Enter to accept the default shown in [brackets].\\n`);\n240: \n241:   const p = new Prompter();\n242:   const deferredWarnings: string[] = [];\n243: \n244:   try {\n245:     const cfg: WomboConfig = structuredClone(DEFAULT_CONFIG);\n246: \n247:     // -- Check git upfront (always required) --------------------------------\n248:     await checkDependency(\n249:       {\n250:         bin: \"git\",\n251:         name: \"git\",\n252:         installHint: \"https://git-scm.com/downloads\",\n253:         requiredBy: \"core (worktrees, branches)\",\n254:       },\n255:       p,\n256:       deferredWarnings\n257:     );\n258: \n259:     // -- General ----------------------------------------------------------\n260:     section(\"General\");\n261:     cfg.tasksDir = await p.string(\"Tasks directory\", cfg.tasksDir);\n262:     cfg.baseBranch = await p.string(\"Base branch\", cfg.baseBranch);\n263: \n264:     // -- Build ------------------------------------------------------------\n265:     section(\"Build\");\n266:     cfg.build.command = await p.string(\"Build command\", cfg.build.command);\n267:     cfg.build.timeout = await p.number(\"Build timeout (ms)\", cfg.build.timeout);\n268:     cfg.build.artifactDir = await p.string(\"Artifact directory\", cfg.build.artifactDir);\n269: \n270:     // -- Install ----------------------------------------------------------\n271:     section(\"Install\");\n272:     cfg.install.command = await p.string(\"Install command\", cfg.install.command);\n273:     cfg.install.timeout = await p.number(\"Install timeout (ms)\", cfg.install.timeout);\n274: \n275:     // -- Git --------------------------------------------------------------\n276:     section(\"Git\");\n277:     cfg.git.branchPrefix = await p.string(\"Branch prefix\", cfg.git.branchPrefix);\n278:     cfg.git.worktreePrefix = await p.string(\"Worktree prefix\", cfg.git.worktreePrefix);\n279:     cfg.git.remote = await p.string(\"Remote name\", cfg.git.remote);\n280:     cfg.git.mergeStrategy = await p.string(\"Merge strategy flag\", cfg.git.mergeStrategy);\n281: \n282:     // -- Agent ------------------------------------------------------------\n283:     section(\"Agent\");\n284:     cfg.agent.bin = await p.stringOrNull(\"Agent binary path (or 'auto')\", cfg.agent.bin);\n285:     cfg.agent.name = await p.string(\"Agent name\", cfg.agent.name);\n286:     cfg.agent.configFiles = await p.stringList(\n287:       \"Config files to copy (comma-sep)\",\n288:       cfg.agent.configFiles\n289:     );\n290:     cfg.agent.tmuxPrefix = await p.string(\"Multiplexer session prefix\", cfg.agent.tmuxPrefix);\n291:     const muxPref = await p.string(\n292:       \"Multiplexer preference (auto/dmux/tmux)\",\n293:       cfg.agent.multiplexer\n294:     );\n295:     if (muxPref === \"auto\" || muxPref === \"dmux\" || muxPref === \"tmux\") {\n296:       cfg.agent.multiplexer = muxPref;\n297:     } else {\n298:       console.log(`  Invalid multiplexer \"${muxPref}\", using \"auto\".`);\n299:       cfg.agent.multiplexer = \"auto\";\n300:     }\n301: \n302:     // Check multiplexer availability\n303:     if (cfg.agent.multiplexer === \"dmux\") {\n304:       await checkDependency(\n305:         {\n306:           bin: \"dmux\",\n307:           name: \"dmux\",\n308:           installHint: \"cargo install dmux  or  https://github.com/nicholasgasior/dmux\",\n309:           requiredBy: \"multiplexer (agent.multiplexer = dmux)\",\n310:         },\n311:         p,\n312:         deferredWarnings\n313:       );\n314:     } else if (cfg.agent.multiplexer === \"tmux\") {\n315:       await checkDependency(\n316:         {\n317:           bin: \"tmux\",\n318:           name: \"tmux\",\n319:           installHint: \"https://github.com/tmux/tmux\",\n320:           requiredBy: \"multiplexer (agent.multiplexer = tmux)\",\n321:         },\n322:         p,\n323:         deferredWarnings\n324:       );\n325:     } else {\n326:       // \"auto\" — check both, warn only if neither is found\n327:       const hasDmux = isBinAvailable(\"dmux\");\n328:       const hasTmux = isBinAvailable(\"tmux\");\n329:       if (!hasDmux && !hasTmux) {\n330:         console.log(`\\n  \\x1b[33m[WARNING]\\x1b[0m No terminal multiplexer found (dmux or tmux).`);\n331:         console.log(`  Interactive mode (--interactive) requires a multiplexer.`);\n332:         const installTmux = await p.yesNo(\"Attempt to install tmux?\", false);\n333:         if (installTmux) {\n334:           const installed = await tryInstall(\n335:             {\n336:               bin: \"tmux\",\n337:               name: \"tmux\",\n338:               installHint: \"https://github.com/tmux/tmux\",\n339:               requiredBy: \"multiplexer (interactive mode)\",\n340:             },\n341:             p\n342:           );\n343:           if (!installed) {\n344:             deferredWarnings.push(\n345:               \"  - tmux or dmux: needed for interactive mode (--interactive). Install one:\\n\" +\n346:               \"      tmux: https://github.com/tmux/tmux\\n\" +\n347:               \"      dmux: https://github.com/nicholasgasior/dmux\"\n348:             );\n349:           }\n350:         } else {\n351:           deferredWarnings.push(\n352:             \"  - tmux or dmux: needed for interactive mode (--interactive). Install one:\\n\" +\n353:             \"      tmux: https://github.com/tmux/tmux\\n\" +\n354:             \"      dmux: https://github.com/nicholasgasior/dmux\"\n355:           );\n356:         }\n357:       }\n358:     }\n359: \n360:     // -- Agent Registry ---------------------------------------------------\n361:     section(\"Agent Registry (specialized agent downloads)\");\n362:     console.log(\"  Pull specialized agent definitions from an external registry at launch time.\\n\");\n363:     const modePref = await p.string(\n364:       \"Mode (auto/monitored/disabled)\",\n365:       cfg.agentRegistry.mode\n366:     );\n367:     const validModes: AgentRegistryMode[] = [\"auto\", \"monitored\", \"disabled\"];\n368:     if (validModes.includes(modePref as AgentRegistryMode)) {\n369:       cfg.agentRegistry.mode = modePref as AgentRegistryMode;\n370:     } else {\n371:       console.log(`  Invalid mode \"${modePref}\", using \"auto\".`);\n372:       cfg.agentRegistry.mode = \"auto\";\n373:     }\n374:     if (cfg.agentRegistry.mode !== \"disabled\") {\n375:       cfg.agentRegistry.source = await p.string(\n376:         \"Source repo (owner/repo)\",\n377:         cfg.agentRegistry.source\n378:       );\n379:     }\n380: \n381:     // -- Portless ---------------------------------------------------------\n382:     section(\"Portless (localhost server testing)\");\n383:     console.log(\"  Portless prevents port collisions when multiple agents run dev servers.\\n\");\n384:     cfg.portless.enabled = await p.yesNo(\"Enable portless integration\", cfg.portless.enabled);\n385:     if (cfg.portless.enabled) {\n386:       // Check portless availability\n387:       await checkDependency(\n388:         {\n389:           bin: \"portless\",\n390:           name: \"portless\",\n391:           installHint: \"npm install -g portless\",\n392:           requiredBy: \"portless integration (portless.enabled = true)\",\n393:         },\n394:         p,\n395:         deferredWarnings\n396:       );\n397: \n398:       cfg.portless.bin = await p.stringOrNull(\"Portless binary path (or 'auto')\", cfg.portless.bin);\n399:       cfg.portless.proxyPort = await p.number(\"Proxy port\", cfg.portless.proxyPort);\n400:       cfg.portless.https = await p.yesNo(\"Enable HTTPS/HTTP2\", cfg.portless.https);\n401:     }\n402: \n403:     // -- Defaults ---------------------------------------------------------\n404:     section(\"Runtime Defaults\");\n405:     cfg.defaults.maxConcurrent = await p.number(\"Max concurrent agents\", cfg.defaults.maxConcurrent);\n406:     cfg.defaults.maxRetries = await p.number(\"Max retries per agent\", cfg.defaults.maxRetries);\n407: \n408:     // -- Write all operative files -----------------------------------------\n409:     console.log(`\\n${\"─\".repeat(60)}`);\n410: \n411:     // Ensure .wombo-combo/ directory exists before writing any files\n412:     const womboDir = resolve(opts.projectRoot, WOMBO_DIR);\n413:     if (!existsSync(womboDir)) mkdirSync(womboDir, { recursive: true });\n414: \n415:     // 1. config.json\n416:     const json = JSON.stringify(cfg, null, 2) + \"\\n\";\n417:     writeFileSync(configPath, json, \"utf-8\");\n418:     console.log(`\\nCreated ${CONFIG_FILE}`);\n419: \n420:     // 2. tasks/ folder store\n421:     const now = new Date().toISOString();\n422:     const projectName = opts.projectRoot.split(\"/\").pop() ?? \"project\";\n423:     const tasksDirPath = resolve(womboDir, cfg.tasksDir);\n424:     if (existsSync(tasksDirPath) && !opts.force) {\n425:       console.log(`${cfg.tasksDir}/ already exists, skipping.`);\n426:     } else {\n427:       mkdirSync(tasksDirPath, { recursive: true });\n428:       const metaContent = stringifyYaml({\n429:         version: \"1.0\",\n430:         meta: {\n431:           created_at: now,\n432:           updated_at: now,\n433:           project: projectName,\n434:           generator: \"wombo-combo\",\n435:           maintainer: \"user\",\n436:         },\n437:       }, { lineWidth: 120 });\n438:       writeFileSync(resolve(tasksDirPath, \"_meta.yml\"), metaContent, \"utf-8\");\n439:       console.log(`Created ${WOMBO_DIR}/${cfg.tasksDir}/ with _meta.yml.`);\n440:     }\n441: \n442:     // 3. archive/ folder store\n443:     const archiveDirPath = resolve(womboDir, cfg.archiveDir);\n444:     if (existsSync(archiveDirPath) && !opts.force) {\n445:       console.log(`${cfg.archiveDir}/ already exists, skipping.`);\n446:     } else {\n447:       mkdirSync(archiveDirPath, { recursive: true });\n448:       const archiveMeta = stringifyYaml({\n449:         version: \"1.0\",\n450:         meta: {\n451:           created_at: now,\n452:           updated_at: now,\n453:           project: projectName,\n454:           generator: \"wombo-combo\",\n455:           maintainer: \"user\",\n456:         },\n457:       }, { lineWidth: 120 });\n458:       writeFileSync(resolve(archiveDirPath, \"_meta.yml\"), archiveMeta, \"utf-8\");\n459:       console.log(`Created ${WOMBO_DIR}/${cfg.archiveDir}/.`);\n460:     }\n461: \n462:     // 4. logs/ directory\n463:     const logsDir = resolve(womboDir, \"logs\");\n464:     if (!existsSync(logsDir)) {\n465:       mkdirSync(logsDir, { recursive: true });\n466:       console.log(`Created ${WOMBO_DIR}/logs/`);\n467:     }\n468: \n469:     // 5. history/ directory\n470:     const historyDir = resolve(womboDir, \"history\");\n471:     if (!existsSync(historyDir)) {\n472:       mkdirSync(historyDir, { recursive: true });\n473:       console.log(`Created ${WOMBO_DIR}/history/`);\n474:     }\n475: \n476:     // -- Install agent definition template --------------------------------\n477:     const agentDir = resolve(opts.projectRoot, \".opencode\", \"agents\");\n478:     const agentDefPath = resolve(agentDir, `${cfg.agent.name}.md`);\n479: \n480:     let installAgent = true;\n481:     if (existsSync(agentDefPath) && !opts.force) {\n482:       installAgent = await p.yesNo(\n483:         `.opencode/agents/${cfg.agent.name}.md already exists. Overwrite?`,\n484:         false\n485:       );\n486:     }\n487: \n488:     if (installAgent) {\n489:       mkdirSync(agentDir, { recursive: true });\n490:       const agentTemplate = renderAgentTemplate(cfg, opts.projectRoot);\n491:       writeFileSync(agentDefPath, agentTemplate, \"utf-8\");\n492:       console.log(`Created .opencode/agents/${cfg.agent.name}.md from template.`);\n493:     } else {\n494:       console.log(`.opencode/agents/${cfg.agent.name}.md already exists, skipping.`);\n495:     }\n496: \n497:     // Migrate: remove legacy agent/ from configFiles if present\n498:     const legacyIdx = cfg.agent.configFiles.indexOf(\"agent/\");\n499:     if (legacyIdx !== -1) {\n500:       cfg.agent.configFiles.splice(legacyIdx, 1);\n501:       const updatedJson = JSON.stringify(cfg, null, 2) + \"\\n\";\n502:       writeFileSync(configPath, updatedJson, \"utf-8\");\n503:       console.log(`Removed legacy agent/ from configFiles (agents now live in .opencode/agents/).`);\n504:     }\n505: \n506:     // -- Deferred dependency warnings -------------------------------------\n507:     if (deferredWarnings.length > 0) {\n508:       console.log(`\\n\\x1b[33m── Missing Dependencies ─────────────────────────────────────\\x1b[0m`);\n509:       console.log(`The following tools were not found and should be installed`);\n510:       console.log(`before running wombo-combo:\\n`);\n511:       for (const warning of deferredWarnings) {\n512:         console.log(warning);\n513:       }\n514:       console.log();\n515:     }\n516: \n517:     console.log(`\\nYou're all set! Run 'woco help' to see available commands.\\n`);\n518:   } finally {\n519:     p.close();\n520:   }\n521: }\n\n(End of file - total 521 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/init.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * init.ts — Interactive guided setup for .wombo-combo/config.json.\n *\n * Usage: woco init [--force]\n *\n * Walks the user through every config section, showing defaults and\n * accepting overrides.  Press Enter on any prompt to keep the default.\n *\n * Key behaviors:\n *   - Checks for required external tools (git, tmux/dmux, portless) when\n *     the user selects options that depend on them.\n *   - If a tool is missing, offers to install it or defers a reminder to\n *     the end of init.\n *   - Creates all operative files: config.json, tasks.yml, archive.yml,\n *     state.json, logs/, history/.\n *   - Ensures the .wombo-combo/ directory exists before writing anything.\n */\n\nimport { existsSync, writeFileSync, readFileSync, mkdirSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { resolve } from \"node:path\";","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773435237856,"end":1773435237859}}}}
