{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435302160,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fb18f3001C2fHaZUPmCSF89","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fb0ff0001mitBEuw0D5keMe","type":"text","text":"### Step 2: Add TDD section to generalist-agent.md template\n\nThe TDD section should be conditionally injected by the templates.ts rendering logic, not hardcoded in the template. Following the same pattern as the portless block, I'll add the TDD instructions as a constant block in templates.ts and inject it conditionally. But first, let me also look at how the `Workflow` section in the generalist template can be updated to incorporate TDD when enabled.\n\nThe approach: The TDD block will be injected before \"## What You Must Never Do\" (same pattern as portless). When TDD is enabled, the workflow section should also reference the TDD cycle. Since the workflow is in the template itself, I'll handle this by injecting a separate TDD section.","time":{"start":1773435302159,"end":1773435302159}}}
