{"type":"text","timestamp":1773435450029,"sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","part":{"id":"prt_ce8fd3faf0028Fv3EusxTpgni3","sessionID":"ses_3170615afffe9yXhPnqCvGyAra","messageID":"msg_ce8fd36d60012DKPLWABelm75b","type":"text","text":"Everything passes. Let me provide a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**3 commits on `feature/tdd-agent-prompt-integration`:**\n\n1. **`src/config.ts`** — Added `TddConfig` interface and integrated it into `WomboConfig`:\n   - New `TddConfig` type with `enabled` (boolean) and `testCommand` (string) fields\n   - Default values: `enabled: false`, `testCommand: \"bun test\"`\n   - Validation: ensures `testCommand` is non-empty when TDD is enabled\n\n2. **`src/lib/templates.ts`** — Added TDD block injection for agent definitions:\n   - `TDD_BLOCK` constant with comprehensive red-green-refactor instructions covering all 5 steps (write failing test → verify failure → write minimal code → verify pass → refactor)\n   - `buildTddBlock()` helper to substitute `{{testCommand}}` placeholder\n   - Conditional injection in `renderGeneralistAgent()` — inserts before \"## What You Must Never Do\" (same pattern as portless)\n   - Conditional injection in `patchImportedAgent()` — appends to body after portless block\n\n3. **`src/lib/prompt.ts`** — Added TDD section to per-task agent prompts:\n   - Injects a concise TDD workflow and rules section when `config.tdd.enabled` is true\n   - Uses the configured test command from `config.tdd.testCommand`\n\n4. **`src/commands/init.ts`** — Added TDD section to the setup wizard:\n   - Prompts user for TDD enabled/disabled and test command during `woco init`\n   - Follows the existing pattern (placed between Portless and Runtime Defaults sections)\n\n### Design Decisions\n\n- **Conditional injection, not static template content**: Following the established pattern (portless, browser testing), TDD instructions are injected programmatically based on `config.tdd.enabled`. The agent never sees \"if TDD is enabled\" prose — it either gets the instructions or doesn't.\n- **Disabled by default**: `tdd.enabled: false` — users opt in during `woco init` or by editing `config.json`\n- **`bun test` as default**: Uses Bun's built-in test runner as specified in the task description\n- **No new dependencies**: Pure code changes to existing files","time":{"start":1773435450028,"end":1773435450028}}}
